I personally prefer Guava's immutable collections:<p><pre><code>    List<String> fruits = ImmutableList.of("apple", "orange", "pear");
</code></pre>
It also works for sets and maps:<p><pre><code>    Set<String> fruits = ImmutableSet.of("apple", "orange", "pear");
    Map<String, Integer> fruitCounts = ImmutableMap.of("apple", 3, "orange", 2, "pear", 6);

</code></pre>
